[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[span class="ir"]]04/17 1█:█3 |[[/span]] Research Site-79 (Tokushima, Japan) reports the production of extant [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]] by several [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243-A[[/span]] instances. Logistics is notified and begins rerouting extant [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]] to various fallback sites.

[[span class="ir"]]04/17 █7:██ |[[/span]] Site-79 reports full production of [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]] by all (respective) [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243-A[[/span]] instances, indicating a comprehensive failure of its dedicated supply line within ~80 hours. Logistics halts relevant operations for immediate inspection.

----

[[span class="ir"]]04/18 0█:0█ |[[/span]] Containment Site-50 (Tokyo, Japan) reports full production of [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]] by all (respective) [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243-A[[/span]] instances, indicating a collective failure of Japan's dedicated supply lines. Additional Logistics personnel are deployed for inspection.

[[span class="ir"]]04/18 09:██ -- ██:47 |[[/span]] Logistics is unable to discern cause of eventual supply failure. Local fallback [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]] facilities have exceeded capacity; supply lines are resumed to redirect excess [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]] to Australian fallback sites. Within the following 8-hour duration, Containment Sites-36, -45, -84 report full production of [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]], indicating a complete failure of all dedicated supply lines across Asia, Australia, and Eastern Europe.

----

[[span class="ir"]]04/19 █0:█3 |[[/span]] Logistics is unable to deploy sufficient personnel for situational assessment. [[span class="diss"]]Acroamatic Abatement[[/span]] personnel are notified of an impending event of unclear nature, and begin rigorous inspection of [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]] and relevant delivery systems (while still operational).

[[span class="ir"]]04/19 17:█0 |[[/span]] Various Foundation facilities across Western Europe begin to report similar failures of existential [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]Acroamatic Abatement[[/span]] personnel discover that these failures have been occurring at a roughly consistent rate; the effect appears to be spreading outward, radially, from Site-79.

----

[[span class="ir"]]04/20 ██:38 |[[/span]] Total existential [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]] failure reported across all Sites outside North America. Overwatch Command and Parachronology are informed of an impending global [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]] failure of unknown origin. Emergency transport contingencies are immediately activated worldwide to alleviate near-critical buildups of extant [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]]. Parachronology begins lateral chronological analysis protocol to determine likelihood of chronological or other reality-shift. ATF [[span class="diss"]]Digamma-7243[[/span]] are immediately called to their posts within [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]].

[[span class="ir"]]04/20 ██:21 |[[/span]] Due to loss of .AIC-powered communication encryption services (via [/scp-6488 RAIDFRAME VIII]), Chinese militia groups intercept Logistics' communications regarding the ongoing emergent scenario. Mainland China's government refuses entry to Logistics' transport vessels, citing direct order of the Global Occult Coalition. Contingency systems are unable to account for critical buildup of esoteric substances, resulting in a catastrophic hazardous materials breach. Sites-50, -79 are lost.

[[span class="ir"]]04/20 █8:4█ |[[/span]] Facilities across North America's Western Coast begin to experience existential [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]] failure. [[span class="diss"]]Acroamatic Abatement[[/span]] corrects their prior analysis, having determined that the predicted locus of failure is not Site-79, but [[span class="diss"]]Site-43[[/span]], in reverse order of proximity. All but one of ATF [[span class="diss"]]Digamma-7243[[/span]] have reported to [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]]. The following SMS correspondence occurs between Taskforce Commander Dr. Reynders and Place H. MD., PhD.:

[[div class="sms"]]

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] Get back here immediately. Give me your ETA as soon as you know it.

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] We need you. NOW

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] Where are you

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] Don't you dare forward my calls. I am not to be ignored.

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] PICK
> UP
> YOUR
> PHONE

[[div class="table6"]]
> [[span class="mcd"]]P:[[/span]] When do you need me there?
[[/div]]

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] NOW. PICK UP THE PHONE

[[div class="table6"]]
> [[span class="mcd"]]P:[[/span]] I'm busy.
> I've got a time-traveling, universe-hopping teleportation machine. I'm sure I'll be where I need to be, when I need to be.
[[/div]]

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] What the HELL is wrong with you? UNDER NO CIRCUMSTANCES will you fly into the eye of an esoteric hurricane with that THING

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] WHY ARE YOU AT 87

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] PICK UP
[[/div]]

[[span class="ir"]]04/20 2█:██ |[[/span]] The Logistics Branch is unable to discern procedural cause of failure. The [[span class="diss"]]Acroamatic Abatement Section[[/span]] is unable to discern any fault in [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]]'s operation, or that of the [[span class="diss"]]DePLExA Engine[[/span]] itself. Parachronology is unable to detect any symptoms of imminent CK-Class, ZK-Class, or other XK-Class event. The Temporal Anomalies Department forecasts a 0% probability of any impending reality shift, chronological shift, temporal pivot, timeline branch, timeline merge, or other possible cause of [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] malfunction. The [*/scp-7579 Temporality Annex] is unresponsive.

----

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 0█:0█ |[[/span]] The Astronomy Department reports sudden activity from [*/scp-179 SCP-179]. It holds its head in its hands, apparently sobbing. Meaning unclear.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 01:██ |[[/span]] Total existential [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]] failure has occurred across all relevant facilities, except those within ~1000km of [[span class="diss"]]Site-43[[/span]]. Several more fallback facilities have failed; contingency systems are beyond capacity. Further SMS correspondence occurs between Dr. Reynders and Dr. PHMD.:

[[div class="sms"]]

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] Neither of us is stupid. [[span class="diss"]]I know what you are. I know you've been planning something.[[/span]]

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] [[span class="diss"]]You may have everyone else fooled.[[/span]] But if we live to see tomorrow, know this:

> [[span class="ir"]]R:[[/span]] [[span class="diss"]]I'm going to stop you.[[/span]]

[[/div]]

Implications unclear.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 █2:██ |[[/span]] With no discernable indication of the impending event's nature, it is presumed by default that some oblique malfunction of [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] will be responsible. Dr. Reynders proposes the deactivation of [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] immediately following the delivery of all remaining [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]] //in absentia//, as those non-materials must be voided into [[span class="diss"]]its aperture[[/span]] to prevent a ZK-Class temporal paradox.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 █4:3█ |[[/span]] O5 Council reports that extra-universal parties and contingency groups are entirely unresponsive. Emergency Protocol "VEILBREAK" enacted; all available resources redirected toward [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]], cleanup and contingency efforts. [*/scp-2000 SCP-2000] activated in standby mode.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 0█:█7 |[[/span]] Dr. Reynders convenes remotely with O5 Council; she is incidentally informed of blacksite Facility-6488, in which RAIDFRAME VIII (LOTUS) is housed. She is then informed of the true nature of LOTUS' origin and operation, as well as its imminent planned deactivation. Dr. Reynders attempts to warn the Council of the potential ramifications of LOTUS' deactivation, but the connection is abruptly terminated by unknown means.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:14 |[[/span]] Further correspondence between Dr. Reynders and Dr. PHMD.:

[[div class="sms"]]

[[div class="table6"]]
> [[span class="mcd"]]P:[[/span]] [[span class="diss"]]You know how it goes.[[/span]]
[[/div]]

[[/div]]

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 06:██ |[[/span]] Dr. Reynders proceeds to disassemble and jury-rig nearby terminal components into a makeshift broadcast system. She attempts to hail Facility-6488 and all nearby Sites, calling for any available respondents. //[[span class="diss"]]But nobody came.[[/span]]//

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 0█:2█ |[[/span]] As the final wastecarte approaches [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243's central aperture[[/span]], all remaining ATF personnel and maintenance technicians prepare for the first ever complete deactivation of [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]].

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 █6:██ |[[/span]] LOTUS begins its deactivation sequence, causing an unprecedented release of highly deviant artificial intelligences into various digital systems, globally and beyond.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 █6:█9 |[[/span]] [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] successfully commences shutdown. No faults are detected. Dr. Deering begins arguing with Dr. Reynders, maintaining the position that their deactivation of [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is the very event which retroactively caused global existential [[span class="diss"]]abatement[[/span]] failure.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 █6:██ |[[/span]] ███X-MCD/II (the "Paradox Exodus Engine") is co-opted by rogue AI, causing it and Dr. PHMD.'s demanifestation from consensus reality. Dr. Reynders' further attempts to contact him are unsuccessful.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:██ |[[/span]] Dr. Deering is interrupted mid-harangue by the spontaneous re-activation of [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]]. All internal cores hyper-activate, triggering chronological reinforcement contingency protocols. Dr. Reynders orders the immediate shutdown of [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] via analog manual override. Maintenance personnel report confusion as [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]]'s P. A. system broadcasts conflicting instructions in a near-perfect imitation of Dr. Reynders' voice.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:██ |[[/span]] Dr. Deering approaches Chief [[span class="diss"]]Torosyan-[[/span]]Deering, procures a heavily modified TAD //[*/scp-6500/offset/15 jumpwatch]// from his uniform pocket, and begins tapping it in frantic rhythm. Dr. Reynders exclaims, pulling Dr. Deering toward herself and attempting to stop him. The device activates, causing both to disappear.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:██ |[[/span]] As [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]]'s latent stores of extant [[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]] (and paradoxically-reinstated non-[[span class="diss"]]effluence[[/span]]) approach critical [[span class="diss"]]recondicity[[/span]], an intense red hue begins to permeate [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]]. Multiple possible iterations of Drs. [[span class="diss"]]McInnis[[/span]] and [[span class="diss"]]Ngo[[/span]] manifest and overlap, signaling an imminent Copenhagen decoherence event. Chief [[span class="diss"]]Torosyan-[[/span]]Deering vocalizes distress, and quickly exits [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]].

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:██ |[[/span]] Local time (as measured by all electronic devices) cycles rapidly through the calendar year. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]]'s scheduled automatic reference check triggers one hundred and twenty-two times in quick succession. Apparitions of Dr. Deering, who remains absent, attempt to override this every three seconds. In his absence between attempts, the override is deemed inauthentic. [[span class="diss"]]The device[[/span]] is unable to locate sufficient anchors for its definitive chronology, and is forced to utilize a probabilistic metric; multiple attempted microadjustments overlap in local spacetime. A large film projector reel manifests within Dr. [[span class="diss"]]Ngo[[/span]]'s skull, killing her instantly. Iterations of Dr. [[span class="diss"]]McInnis[[/span]] draw concealed weapons and fire upon each other simultaneously. Maintenance personnel begin to sever their own fingers, and uncontrollably consume the lost blood.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:██ |[[/span]] A fourth sublevel manifests between [[span class="diss"]]Site-43[[/span]] and [[span class="diss"]]AAF-X[[/span]], containing [[span class="diss"]]two elderly humanoid figures[[/span]]. They are immediately aerosolized by ambient thaumic bloom and incorporated into a coruscating halo suffusing the bedrock. [[span class="diss"]]Acroamatic[[/span]] decontainment events increase in frequency and severity sevenfold.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:██ |[[/span]] Chief [[span class="diss"]]Torosyan-[[/span]]Deering sprints down a narrow hallway toward the Emergency [[span class="diss"]]Acroamatic Redundancy[[/span]] Bunker. [[span class="diss"]]She[[/span]] trips over [[span class="diss"]]the corpse of[[/span]] Chief [[span class="diss"]]A. Torosyan-[[/span]]Deering, and is knocked unconscious by the fall.

[[span class="ir"]]04/21 ██:██ |[[/span]] [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] initiates chronological reinforcement. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] explodes. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] implodes. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is [[span class="diss"]]The Breach That Keeps On Breaching[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is [[span class="diss"]]THEREISNOCANNON[[/span]]. The [[span class="diss"]]DePLExA Engine[[/span]] is not itself. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] was [[span class="diss"]]a 130 sqft room located inside Provisional Outpost-A904, a faux two-story home in suburban Garrett Park, Maryland, USA[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is [[span class="diss"]]EXISTENTIAL ABATEMENT[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] will be [[span class="diss"]]The Common (?) Denominator[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is [[span class="diss"]]{{what you've all been waiting for}}[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] must not exist. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] must exist. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is [[span class="diss"]]the infinite deaths of {{Philip Eugene Deering}}[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is [[span class="diss"]]the infinite failures of {{Dougall Alton Deering}}[[/span]]. [[span class="diss"]]SCP-7243[[/span]] is [[span class="diss"]]{{an anti-idea, a cosmic joke, a tumorous idol, a recursive deceit}}. So are we all.[[/span]]

