[[/span]]

"Nexus-7243" is a designation. [[span style="filter: opacity(0.66)"]]--This designation was created to reference [[span class="diss"]]a location[[/span]]-- 
--"Nexus-7243" was created to designate [[span class="diss"]]a vague absence of location; {{an everything into which no pattern can scream}}[[/span]]--
[[/span]]

This designation (hereafter AO-"NX-7243") was created to facilitate communication [[span class="diss"]]regarding its reference[[/span]]. However, AO-"NX-7243"'s intended usage is rendered impossible, as it is subject to an [[span class="diss"]]intense dissociative[[/span]] effect. [[span style="filter: opacity(0.66);"]]--Any attempt to propagate data regarding AO-"NX-7243"'s [[span class="diss"]]reference is targeted by the [[/span]]--[[/span]]

[[span style="filter: opacity(0.66);"]]--This effect [[span class="diss"]]appears[[/span]] to permeate data regarding any [[span class="diss"]]location[[/span]] AO-"NX-7243" might reference--
--The effect [[span class="diss"]]is self-affecting[[/span]]--
--The effect [[span class="diss"]]cannot meaningfully be described[[/span]]--
[[/span]]

AO-"NX-7243"'s intended usage is inhibited by an effect. Said inhibition is not apparently caused by any of the following effects, in isolation:

* lesser antimemetic effect (un-retainable)
* greater antimemetic effect (incomprehensible)
* semiontological hazard
* cognitohazard
* narrativohazard
* localized micro-CK-Class "communicative retcon"
* miscellaneous chronological shift
* extra-Noöspherism
* the 'Deletion effect'
* ontokinesis

[[>]]
[[span style="filter: opacity(0.66);"]]{{//# note to self: review other dept analyses before publishing file//}}[[/span]]
[[/>]]

Due to the recent influx of highly deviant artificial intelligences, the role of digital subterfuge in the effect cannot be ruled out; supposing there is none, it would stand to reason that AO-"NX-7243"'s intended usage is inhibited at a fundamental informational level, possibly a macroscopic quantum phenomenon. [[span style="filter: opacity(0.66);"]]--This inhibition extends to any alternative designation which would share its [[span class="diss"]]item of reference[[/span]] with [[span class="diss"]]that[[/span]] of AO-"NX-72--[[/span]]

In any case, the phenomenon propagates to any term whose intended function is uniquely and practically similar to that of AO-"NX-7243".

