[[table]]
[[row]]
[[hcell]]
[[div class="blockquote"]]
[[div style="text-align: center !important"]]
//[...]//
[[/div]]

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You're trying to fix your old mistakes, but you keep making new ones in the process. That needs to stop. Now.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] I don't think--

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You think too much, actually, but never about the right things. You think about how unfair it is, you think about how it's not your fault, but you never examine your motivations. Your job, doctor, is to resolve the abatement crisis. You've only been pretending to do that. The world's //fucking// toilets are overflowing, and here you are plunging down your back-clog of guilt on our borrowed time.

[[span class="dd"]]Dr. Deering:[[/span]] That's not... fair. It's...

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]]  It's what you deserve to hear. You keep fucking up, and every time you do, you wait for someone to tell you it's okay. Well, it isn't okay. It isn't okay that you're wasting our final opportunities in favour of feeling sorry for yourself. That's over as of this moment. You need Phil to forgive you? He can't. He's dead. You need me to do it?

= //<Silence on recording.>//

[[span class="at"]]Chief Torosyan-Deering:[[/span]] You've worn me down. I'm sick of your bullshit. I forgive you. Now take responsibility, Doug, and //do your fucking job.//

[[div style="text-align: center !important"]]
//[...]//
[[/div]]
[[/div]]
[[/hcell]]
[[/row]]
[[/table]]

@@ @@

[[div class="notation at"]]
When my resolve slipped, I promised myself I'd track down that supercilious twit and let him have it with both barrels, as a victory treat.

But every time I clawed out my new temporary haven after that damnable annual reset, I imagined what it would be like to dig myself out entirely and meet him digging inward from the other side, as I knew he would be, and I couldn't find my nerve. Maybe I'd long since lost it. He'd be trying, for the first time, actually trying, and also for the first time I found that wasn't nothing. Wasn't entirely without meaning.

I simply haven't got the energy to hate anymore. Hating him, and my prison, and this ridiculous unending nightmare-- it's burned through everything else I ever had. It's just him and me, now, and what he said in a puff of selfish navel-gazing is finally true: we understand each other.

We both want this to be over.
[[/div]]

@@ @@

